race.comment: NOBLE DECREE (1) resumes here but the form he showed when last in work was full of merit. Revved up for this with a recent trial and maps ideally from gate two. Will prove very hard to toss. Former Stokes galloper CHEVAL CHIC (4) is having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she was facing down south. Respect any market confidence. DREAM LANTERN (5) returned in good order with a strong win around this circuit and will have come on with that run now under the belt. Expected to feature prominently again. FLYING SHELLY (10) strips fitter second-up from the break and must be respected from the Vandyke stable. In the mix. THE GAMBLING GREEK (7) next best despite the wide draw.
